Algae

Algae singular ) informal for large, diverse of eukaryotic organisms are not necessarily closely related, and is Included organisms microalgae, such the diatoms, to multicellular such the kelp, brown alga may grow up to 50 m in are aquatic and autotrophic and lack many the and such as xylem, and plants. largest most complex are called while most freshwater forms a green algae which example, "Spirogyra" stoneworts.

